To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All contracts, grants, memorandums of agreement (MOAs), memorandums of understanding (MOUs), and non-disclosure agreements (NDAs) between the Seattle Police Department and the Seattle Police Foundation.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rose Terse

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Florida Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following records:

Hello please produce all records/cases and pertaining files for any cases involving D/S Foster and or D/S Metz and Mason C. Turner DOB June 2,1997 

If redactions are made, please provide the state statute pertaining to the redaction as required by state law.

Also please provide a direct download link for the information or reply to this email with the information attachment as PBSO's information gathering and login system is not in compliance with state or federal law, and it cannot be required.

There should be no fees associated with this request. I would ask that this request be filled via email attachment per Florida Sunshine Law.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Mason C. Turner

To Whom It May Concern:

During the Evanston City Council Meeting on January 8, 2024 councilmember Krissie Harris said “I got some emails as well from residents just asking questions about it.”[1] referring to concerns regarding Flock Safety surveillance cameras in Evanston. Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., we hereby request all emails sent or received by city councilmembers:

– Daniel Biss
– Clare Kelly
– Krissie Harris
– Melissa A. Wynne
– Jonathan Nieuwsmaa
– Bobby Burns
– Thomas M. Suffredin
– Eleanor Revelle
– Devon Reid
– Juan Geracaris

from January 1, 2022 and the date this request is processed (inclusive of those dates) that pertain to automatic license plate reader (ALPR) cameras and/or contain the following keywords:

– "ALPR"
– "automated license plate reader"
– "license plate"
– "cameras"
– "surveillance"

[1] Youtube video of Evanston City Council Meeting 1-8-2024 <https://youtu.be/PyyfBlKwRXI?t=8726>

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Niles Coalition
